item.title: Machine Learning Terminology
item.description: Labels A label is the thing we’re predicting ex: email is spam or not spam Features A feature is an input variable. A simple machine learning project might use a single feature, while a more sophisticated machine learning project could use millions of features spam detector ex: words in email text sender’s address time of email email contains the phrase “one weird trick” Examples An example is a particular instance of data.
